So. There is a new baby in your life. Whether it's your friends, yours, a family members, and you really want to buy them a beautiful book! All you can think of are the classics, and you just know that everyone else is running along those same lines of thought.
<br>&nbsp;

Well, here is a handy list of a couple of my favorites that are clever, cute, and most of all, shouldn't make a parent dread re-reading them a million times.

Little Pea by Amy Krouse Rosenthal illustrated by Jen Corace

<br>![](data:image/png;base64,)Meet Little Pea. He is a happy little guy who loves hanging out with his pea pals, playing with Papa Pea, and snuggling with Momma Pea. But one thing Little Pea doesn't like is CANDY (which is what Peas eat for dinner apparently). But to get to dessert (spinach - Little Pea's FAVORITE) he has to finish every bite of dinner! Blech!
